) TL (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF4FFF6B9C0EFB91FB4334A4" author="De La Cruz-Aguero" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="De La Cruz-Aguero" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" refId="ref274333" refString="De La Cruz-Aguero, J., Martinez, M. A., Cota-Gomez, V. M. &amp; De La Cruz-Aguero, G. (1997) Catalogo de los Peces Marinos de Baja California Sur. Centro Interdiscipinario de Ciencias Marinas." type="book" year="1997">
De La Cruz-Agüero 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF4FFF6B9D1FFB91FFDC3478" box="[1378,1437,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">et al.</emphasis>
1997
</bibRefCitation>
). Metlakatla, south-eastern Alaska (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF4FFF6B9AEAFB75F93934A4" author="Karinen" box="[663,888,1158,1185]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Karinen" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" pagination="1983" refId="ref289290" refString="Karinen, J. F., Wing, B. L. &amp; Straty, R. R. (1985) Records and sightings of fish and invertebrates in the eastern Gulf of Alaska and oceanic phenonmenon related to the 1983 El Nino event. In: Wooster, W. S. &amp; Fluherty, D. L. (Eds.), El Nino North: Nino Effects in the Eastern Subarctic Pacific Ocean. Washington Sea Grant Program, University of Washington, Seattle." type="book chapter" year="1985">
Karinen 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF4FFF6B9A86FB75F97434A4" box="[763,821,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">et al.</emphasis>
1985
</bibRefCitation>
; see comment under 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D43FF4FFF6B9C17FB75FF6934A5" baseAuthorityName="Bloch" baseAuthorityYear="1786" box="[1130,1320,1159,1185]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balistidae" genus="Melichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF4FFF6B9C17FB75FF6934A5" box="[1130,1320,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Melichthys niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below) to San Antonio (about 
<geoCoordinate id="EE235007FF4FFF6B99D8FB59F84534C0" box="[421,516,1195,1221]" degrees="33" direction="south" minutes="32" orientation="latitude" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" precision="925" value="-33.533333">33°32’S</geoCoordinate>
), central 
<collectingCountry id="F3007650FF4FFF6B9A16FB59F8E934C0" box="[619,680,1195,1221]" name="Chile" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF4FFF6B9AC8FB59F97234C0" author="Brito" box="[693,819,1195,1221]" firstAuthor="Brito" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" pagination="77 - 83" refId="ref265822" refString="Brito, J. L. (2003) Nuevos registros de Balistes polylepis (Balistidae), Sphoeroides lobatus (Tetraodontidae), Mola mola y M. ramsayi (Molidae) en San Antonio, Chile (Pisces, Tetraodontiformes). Investigaciones Marinas, Valparaiso, 31, 77 - 83." type="journal article" year="2003">Brito 2003</bibRefCitation>
), including Gulf of California (Bussing in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF4FFF6B9D71FB59FB4034EC" author="Fischer" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Fischer" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" refId="ref278931" refString="Fischer, W., Krupp, F., Schneider, W., Sommer, C., Carpenter, K. E. &amp; Niem, V. H. (1995) Guia FAO para la identificacion para los fines de la pesca. Pacifico centro-oriental. Volume II, Vertebrados, Parte 1. Volume III, Vertebrados, Parte 2. FAO, Rome." type="book" year="1995">
Fischer 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF4FFF6B9D18FB59FFDC34C0" box="[1381,1437,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">et al.</emphasis>
1995
</bibRefCitation>
), Islas Galápagos (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF4FFF6B99AFFB3DF94634EC" author="Grove and Lavenberg" box="[466,775,1231,1257]" firstAuthor="Grove" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" refId="ref284033" refString="Grove, J. S. &amp; Lavenberg, R. J. (1997) The Fishes of the Galapagos Islands. Stanford University Press, Stanford." type="book" year="1997">Grove and Lavenberg 1997</bibRefCitation>
), and Hawai’i (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF4FFF6B9BCDFB3DFE9034EC" author="Randall and Mundy" box="[944,1233,1231,1257]" firstAuthor="Randall" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" pagination="322 - 333" refId="ref315857" refString="Randall, J. &amp; Mundy, B. C. (1998) Balistes polylepis and Xanthichthys caeruleolineatus, two large triggerfishes (Tetraodontiformes: Balistidae) from the Hawaiian Islands, with a key to Hawaiian species. Pacific Science, 52, 322 - 333." type="journal article" year="1998">Randall and Mundy 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Only one Alaska record and isolated records from Washington to California; most common south of California (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF4FFF6B98BBFAE5FB423534" box="[198,259,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">et al.</emphasis>
2002). Benthic; depth: 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FF4FFF6B9A62FAE4F8C63534" box="[543,647,1302,1329]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.57" metricValueMax="5.12" metricValueMin="0.02" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" unit="m" value="257.0" valueMax="512.0" valueMin="2.0">2–512 m</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FF4FFF6B9AE7FAE5F9543537" box="[666,789,1303,1330]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.569464" metricValueMax="5.12064" metricValueMin="0.018288" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" unit="ft" value="843.0" valueMax="1680.0" valueMin="6.0">6–1,680 ft</quantity>
) (min.: Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California; max.: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF4FFF6B9B25FAC9FE003550" author="Miller and Lea" box="[856,1089,1339,1365]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" refId="ref302113" refString="Miller, D. J. &amp; Lea, R. N. (1972) Guide to the coastal marine fishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 157." type="book" year="1972">Miller and Lea 1972</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
